Selenium class 05:
Handling checkboxes and radiobuttons:
---if you only have one checkbox or radiobutton --you can just click on it.
---if you have multiple choices--store them in a list and loop through
DropDown:
---it is the a menu which gives us an opportunity to select one or more option
1. Single select
2. Muliples selects
Handling DropDown:
1. click on dropdown and click on option
2. using Select Class
                in order to use Select Class we need to make sure our dropdown has a select tag
Selecting an option from dropdown can done 3 Ways:
1.by index
2.by visible
3.by value
Whenever you interact with multiple elements you store them inside
the container such as List, Set etc..

In order to deselect the option from dropdown
-- Make sure your DD is multiple select
deselectByValue()
deselectByIndex()
deselectByVisibleText()
deselectAll()

